post_text:
From the New Mexico Activities Association (NMAA): On Thursday, the New Mexico Activities Association Board of Directors passed by a vote of 8-4 that during 2020, summer activities can begin on June 15th. If a school/school district opts to allow for summer activities to take place (which Los Lunas Schools has not made any decisions on a return to play start date as of yet), the guidelines produced by the NMAA must be followed. These guidelines are based on the public health orders set by the Governor of New Mexico and will be updated accordingly. Schools/school districts can implement a later start date and/or stricter guidelines. For Summer 2020, summer programs are under the direction of the NMAA. The NMAA will govern coaching activities during the summer.

https://www.nmact.org/2020/05/nmaa-guidance-for-return-to-play/

post_text: LLMS Tigers iPad returns are next week for 7th & 8th graders who are not returning to LLMS next school year #WeRockLLS
shared_text:
LLMS Tigers
May 19 at 10:54 AM ·

🐯 LLMS iPad drop off:
All 8th graders and any 7th graders ❌not attending LLMS next school year will need to return their iPad to LLMS. 💻

The following are the dates and times that LLMS will be available for iPad drop off:

💙Wednesday May 27 8:00 AM to 12:00 PM
🧡Thursday May 28 8:00 AM to 12:00 PM
💙Friday May 29 8:00 AM to 2:00 PM

There will be a drive through system when returning the iPad. Parents/guardians are to remain in their vehicle during this process. Upon entering the front of the school (off main street), use the bus lanes and you will be met by a school employee. The employee will ask you for student’s name/ID and to show him/her the iPad screen to ensure there are no breaks. The employee will have a plastic bag and ask you to place the iPad, iPad charging cord, and iPad block in the zip lock bag.

We miss our 8th graders and we wish there was a better way to say good bye.

shared_text:
Los Lunas High Lady Tigers Basketball
March 13 at 8:07 AM ·

Good morning Lady Tiger fans, today is the day!! Just a couple of things to share:
We are having a send off today between 4:45- 5 for the girls. We will leave from the high school pool, circle down by the middle school, and then head back up to the freeway. Please join us in making the send off something special for them! With the shutdown off all fans and families this is a weird time for everyone. Also remember we have 3 seniors who will never have the opportunity to play for another state title in front of their family and friends, and we need to show them all of our love and support! Bring signs, wear your tiger gear and be ready to cheer them on as they pass by. Next, we will be having a watch party today at Calvary chapel in Belen. We have a ton of food, and it’s all free to everyone who wants to join! GO TIGERS!!! 🐯🏀🧡💙
